        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add daemonless YouTube transcription fallback",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- fall back to same-origin Android VR direct YouTube audio when `yt-dlp` is missing or fails, then use the configured transcription provider\n- transcribe captionless YouTube videos entirely in the Chrome extension without the daemon using native audio decode, FFmpeg WebAssembly fallback, and browser-cached multilingual Whisper Tiny\n- retain captured SABR playback as a secondary media path, keep explicit `--youtube yt-dlp` and diarization requirements, and exclude the Chrome-only runtime from Firefox builds\n- document the first-use model download; offline model bundling/download workflows are intentionally out of scope\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm -s check` (2259 passed, 42 skipped)\n- `pnpm -s build`\n- `pnpm -C apps/chrome-extension test:chrome` (69 passed, 3 skipped)\n- `pnpm -C apps/chrome-extension build:firefox` (final package directory 796 KB)\n- `SUMMARIZE_LIVE_TESTS=1 pnpm -s vitest run tests/youtube.android-vr.live.test.ts`\n- `SUMMARIZE_LIVE_TESTS=1 pnpm -C apps/chrome-extension exec playwright test -c playwright.config.ts --project=chromium tests/youtube-local.live.spec.ts`\n\nThe extension live test uses a real captionless YouTube video and verifies the actual side-panel flow: current-tab media resolution, signed audio download, browser decoding, local Whisper transcription, and rendered Browser summary.\n",
